review_text: Overall good restaurant. The atmosphere is great, and we were able to find a table immediately. The pasta was fantastic, some of the best I’ve had, but I wouldn’t recommend the pizza. Come here for the pasta however and you’ll have a great time.

Trattoria Demi has become our new favorite Italian restaurant. The staff is friendly, efficient, & helpful. Everything we've tried on the menu has been great, with a couple items definitely shining above the rest. The portions are larger than expected for the prices & delivered to the table hot. The Asiago stuffed gnocchi & homemade lasagna are the must try menu items! The vino pours are fantastic as well!

This is a wonderful Italian restaurant in downtown Evanston. It's quaint and has all the charm of a Italian restaurant like back in the home country. The food is excellent! My wife and I have been to many restaurants and this one meets all the expectations of a fine restaurant that is worth every penny. Be sure to put this place in your list! Venite a gustare il cibo!

I recently had the pleasure of dining at Trattoria Demi, and it was an outstanding experience from start to finish. As this was my first visit, I was thrilled with how it exceeded my expectations.

**Food:** The culinary offerings were spectacular. Each dish was a delightful celebration of flavors, beautifully presented and cooked to perfection. The signature pasta was fresh and bursting with authentic Italian tastes, showcasing the restaurant's attention to detail.

**Service:** The service was impeccable. From the moment I walked in, the staff made me feel welcomed and valued. They were attentive without being intrusive, and ensuring a seamless dining experience.

**Atmosphere:** The ambiance was equally impressive. The warm decor and soft lighting created a cozy yet elegant setting, perfect for enjoying a leisurely meal. The vibrant atmosphere added to the enjoyment.

Overall, my experience at Trattoria Demi was the best I’ve ever had at a restaurant. I left with a full stomach and a big smile, eagerly anticipating my next visit. If you’re looking for exquisite food, stellar service, and a delightful atmosphere, I highly recommend Trattoria Demi!

They served you free breads which is delicious and crunchy outside, soft inside.  The food portion is big.  We ordered small size and barely cannot finish it.  It’s not expensive but the food is nice and served very fast!
Quiet, relaxed, comfortable lunch spot. Good quality bread on the sandwiches; though, the chicken was overcooked, and generally the flavors were a bit bland.
Great little place, with great atmosphere.  Food was delicious.  Service was prompt and friendly.  I would definitely bring the family here to eat.

We happened upon this place in Evanston.  The staff were incredibly welcoming & kind as well as attentive throughout our entire experience.  Our food was delicious & reasonably priced.  I highly recommend stopping in if you are in the area!

I had an evening to myself while staying in Evanston, so I took myself out to dinner at Blind Faith.

It was great! Good portions, lots of choices, and a team that obviously cares about being there.

I had the bibimbap (well seasoned, delicious, very filling), and orange mojito (strong, refreshing, not too sweet), and the chocolate peanut butter cake with raspberry sorbet (rich and satisfying, and decadent for breakfast the next day).

I love this place, the food is excellent. The portions are great. Prices are super high, there are many options for vegans and vegetarians. Our waiter was nice but he forgot about us a few times and there wasn't that many people in the restaurant. I highly recommend this place, hoping you don't get the same waiter.

I enjoyed my wonderful meal.  It's been long while since I last visited.
My server, Charlie, was a pure delight.
It is unfortunate that you no longer have Chili on the menu.

Celebratory Dinner – A Cozy Vegetarian Gem

We visited to celebrate my sister’s upcoming wedding, and despite being a party of fourteen (yes, fourteen!), the staff managed to accommodate us with grace and good humor. It was a tight squeeze, but we made it work—and the cozy, charming ambiance helped set the tone for a joyful evening.

We kicked things off with a trio of appetizers: fried Brussels sprouts, nachos, and stuffed ricotta balls. The Brussels sprouts were crisp and well-prepared, though not my personal favorite. The nachos, however, were a standout—easily the best I’ve ever had, with layers of flavor and perfect crunch. The ricotta balls were satisfying, though they could’ve used a touch more seasoning to really shine.

For my main, I had the spinach lasagna. It was generously portioned and hearty, ideal for a chilly evening. That said, I found myself wishing for a bit of salt and pepper—oddly, none was on the table. I also sampled my dad’s black ginger tofu, which was a hit with the rest of the table but tasted a bit bland to me.

Dessert was a delightful assortment of bite-sized treats: vegan chocolate cupcakes (absolutely divine), almond balls, berry crumble, and a coffee-infused square. The cupcakes stole the show—rich, moist, and indulgent without being heavy.

Overall, this is a solid pick for vegetarians and anyone looking for a welcoming, flavorful dining experience. The staff was friendly, the space was cute, and while a few dishes could use a seasoning boost, the highlights more than made up for it. Would definitely recommend, especially for those nachos and cupcakes!
Delicious! Staff was so friendly, knowledgeable, and accommodating! Loved that they have both vegan and vegetarian meal offerings for our mixed family. 10/10 would recommend!

On Sunday for lunch the restaurant was buzzing with customers but good table was still available. Five stars and double for everything: excellently prepared fresh and tasty dishes, satisfying portions, warm and attentive servers. As a visitor to Chicago, this was the best food and cheerful, comfortable atmosphere that I found.

A great restaurant with a good selection of both vegetarian and vegan dishes on the menu. Friendly staff in a relaxed atmosphere. I recommend the black bean and ginger over jasmine rice and the lasagne (which has cheese). A bonus is the attached bakery - carrot cake, cranberry bars, BFC cupcakes and more. My wife commends the Chai latte with oatmilk.

we only stopped in for coffee so i can't speak to the food, but all of our cups were unfortunately undrinkable. i got a mocha while my husband and our friend got cappuccinos, and all three were pricey (even for the area), took 10 minutes to make during a quiet hour (new trainee?) and frankly barely recognizable as coffee—burnt, watery, and tasteless. i'm sure other things here are okay but if you're seeking a decent cup look elsewhere.

I love this place. I have celiac disease and am vegetarian and they are able to accommodate me so well! Almost everything is gluten free, including the chips! (No cross contamination in the fryer). I love the enchiladas, house salsa, and margaritas. They also have a great brunch, I get the enfrijoladas. Highly recommend dining in because the art and service are amazing, but they do take out as well!

The food here is very good. If you are looking for reasonably priced authentic Mexican food I can not recommend Zentli enough. I had fish tacos which were delicious. I did not order desert but all of my friends did and and they said it was delicious. They also have very good refried beans!

Kicking myself for not getting over here sooner! Sat and the bar with my mom and had the chance to chat with the owner, Piloto. He’s a super talented artist and his mom’s mole straight up rules. Everything we ate was on point and the prices are right. A new go to for refined Mexican

The vibe of this restaurant is so cool, with gorgeous artwork and ambient lighting. The staff were very friendly, our food came out so quickly, and the food was delicious! I got the alambre and al pastor tacos, and a margarita.

Came for dinner around 7:00 pm on a Wednesday evening.  Had reservations and sat right down. Service was good and atmosphere very nice(slightly dark). Great menu, hand shaken drinks.

Very simple chips and Salsa for $5 is my only complaint.  All the food was good. Seasoning could be amped up a bit for my preference. Specifically, the Elote could have been amplified. Bit pricy for overall delivery. I would dine here again
Amazing tacos. Really amazing taste. A little small for the price though. I'm skinny and I could eat 10 of them and they are like 7 dollars a pop. But really really tasty. Def worth a try
Delicious!! The food was outstanding and so was the service. The best mole I’ve ever had! Everything inside is handmade by the owner. From the tables to the art. It’s truly incredible!

Amazing decor , even better food and amazing mixes drinks. Can't say anything bad about this place. It's top notch ! My good friend Ryan brought me over showing me this new spot in my old neighborhood and I couldn't be more delighted to enjoy the amazing food and service. Highly recommend it and will totally be back for more.

Go try it !

The server was so nice! The owner even stopped by and said hi. I had the cauliflower, and it was amazing. So flavorful. We also had the savory monkey bread and chips. Everything was yummy!  Great drinks too.
5 stars every single time.   This time for the opening of Oktoberfest I had the Schweinshaxe with red cabbage.   A truly authentic meal  omg a must have - soooo delicious!

The gluten free fried chicken is amazing and zero reaction. Seems pricey but the portion is beyond generous. My husband and I split it and still had enough left over for a small lunch. I have missed real fried chicken and this hit the spot! They have a dedicated gf fryer

10/10 will definitely come back. We came early on Thursday and it did not disappoint! Mike our waiter was so friendly and helpful - gave a taste of two different wines before ordering a glass and a complimentary flourless chocolate cake (amazing) to celebrate finishing grad school.

We started with the vegan chorizo tacos (UNREAL) and split the trout, general tso cauliflower and broccolini. Everything was so fresh and flavorful!

Here's what you need to know: Outstanding service my Mike Donovan - just a great server who set the standard. Very tasty fried chicken sandwich and ribs. We celebrated our birthday here (very enjoyable galette for dessert) and really enjoyed ourselves and will be back for more, especially for Mike hospitality.

While overall the pricing was fair for the area, The only reason why the review is not 5 stars is because of the pricing on the specials. They had a ribs special that was 4 ribs (about 35-40% of the whole rack) for $33 ($43 with tax and tip) which is just unjustified. These aren't kurobuta heritage ribs that I could tell and good smoking is not an extravagance these days with technology where it is. So seemed excessive for that.

Ambiance is nice and quaint and we look forward to coming back to try the other offerings on the menu.

Meal for 2 with coffee but no alcohol or apps was $100

A Wonderful Dining Experience – Excellent Food & Service!
We stopped by without a reservation and were pleasantly surprised by how accommodating the staff was. They went out of their way to find us a table.
The pork chops were absolutely amazing—perfectly cooked and served with a special sauce that took them to the next level. Every bite was packed with flavor. Our little one had the kids’ chicken, which was both crispy and tender—he loved it!
Overall, a fantastic dining experience with great food and warm hospitality. We’ll definitely be back!

Our best local dining place. I swear every time that I am going to expand my dinner choice, but I always go for the halibut. I would get a side salad versus a salad and an entree because both portions are large enough for a.meal.

Fantastic neighborhood spot with great cocktails and a top to bottom good menu that blends French, Asian, and classic American dishes. All the staff are the best and make you feel right at home. Love this spot.

My family (10 people) came in yesterday to celebrate my mom and aunt's birthday. We had an AMAZING experience! Our server, Beatrice, was truly incredible. The epitome of a great server. She was timely, cleared empty cups/plates between courses, brought napkins and new plates/silverware, and got everyone's order correct, despite many orders having specific modifications. The food was incredible, in particular- the pizza, smoked wings, terriyaki rice bowl with blackened chicken (HUGE portion, made 2 meals out of it!) and the blackened salmon sandwich.

My family has been coming to Bluestone for a long time, and we think they have made awesomely positive changes along the way.

DEFINITELY ask for Beatrice when you go in- you won't regret it!

★★★★★
Blue Stone in Evanston is a hidden gem that perfectly balances casual dining with great food and atmosphere. My group visited during a quiet afternoon, and the experience was fantastic from start to finish.

The appetizers here are generous enough to make a meal! We tried the loaded nachos with chicken, which came perfectly assembled with guacamole, sour cream, and salsa (pro tip: follow our server's recommendation to skip the olives). We also ordered the Parmesan Truffle Fries with aioli, which were absolutely addictive – we demolished them in record time.
The service was outstanding, with both the hostess and our server being incredibly welcoming and knowledgeable. Our server's recommendations were spot-on, helping us make the perfect choices for our meal.

The ambiance is versatile and comfortable, with both booth and table seating options and great lighting throughout. There are TVs placed strategically around the restaurant for sports fans, but they don't detract from the overall chill vibe. During warmer months, they offer outdoor seating which creates a wonderful, relaxing atmosphere. Even in cooler weather, the patio can be enjoyable if you dress appropriately.

Pro tips:
The loaded nachos and truffle fries are must-try items
You can upgrade your entrée's side dish to truffle fries
Visit during off-peak hours if you prefer a quieter atmosphere
Consider the outdoor seating in nice weather

Overall, Blue Stone offers a comfortable, casual dining experience with generous portions and attentive service. Definitely worth checking out if you're in Evanston!

This place has a lot going for it - great service, children-friendly, and nice bar area. However, when it comes to food, it’s… meh. Everything from quesadillas to French onion soup, they were OK but nothing stood out as being outstanding. It is a nice place to stop by for those living near northern part of Evanston but it is not a place one would go out of way as destination.

Come here if you love cracker thin pizza. Careful about extra crispy bc it can burn easily since it's so thin. Don't expect to get full off of pizza alone. Cool atmosphere but can get packed very fast. Kind of hectic with pick up orders on weekend.
Great neighborhood type of place. The canjuin salmon sandwich was very good. Wish I would of taken a picture of it. Pet friendly as well.

Late lunch on a Saturday and the brunch menu was still available. Looked good, but we were more interested in burgers. The menu seems on the pricey side until you experience the generous servings and food quality. Very good. I had the fireman's burger with really delicious, crunchy tater tots and we shared the truffle fries and couldn't finish the large portion. Delicious, though. Burger was great. Jennifer was our server and did everything well, and friendly.
The server  and host were friendly and helpful n the food was delicious and sizeable portions.

I ordered the bbq combo, which includes these excluding the fries, is a good deal at the price. The problem was when you go to eat. The wings, as you can see, were dry as hell. The pulled pork had a gamey taste. The baked beans tasted like straight out of a can. The baked macaroni and cheese was okay, the topping made it dry and it had no flavor. The cornbread was dry and no corn flavor. The only good thing was the coleslaw. I just wish it could have tasted better for the price.

This was the best smokehouse I've been to in a long time... If not ever. They nail it on multiple levels. Service? Amazing. They paid attention to their guests without being overbearing. Food? Best flavors I've experienced. The brisket, chicken, and ribs were excellent. They took great care of my daughter who's in a wheelchair and paid attention to her.

After coming across Pit & Tap on Google and being Intrigued by some of the creative dishes I saw on their menu I had to  stop in.
I tried the smoked wings with Alabama sauce and the Knucklepunch with french fries.
The wings had a lightly smokey flavor to the skin and the meat maintained a nice juicyness.  I thought these were highly enjoyable. I ordered them with the house special Alabama Sauce, but I have no idea what the sauce taste profile was, it was white, but I don't even know how to describe it. 7 wings to an order. Wings are close to 5 stars, the sauce is 3 stars.
The Knucklepunch sounded like an absolute behemoth of a sandwich, it didn't quite live up to my expectations. It was too busy of a sandwich. The most notable take away from this sandwich was the pork belly, It waa just 2 thick peppered slices of fat that needed more rendering to be edible. I did think the smash burger had a nice taste and might be good in the right application. This is the sandwich that finally taught me that more is not necessarily better.
The fries here were the high spot. Fresh cut and exactly the type of fry I remember restaurants for having. These were unsalted so if you want them salted you'll have to ask. I could eat a mountain of these and they'd probably be next level awesome with a good white cheese sauce.
I carried my order out after placing my order online and the lady was beyond pleasant and smiled with her every word. I also thought that the restaurant had a nice set up in a nice neighborhood.
For my next visit whenever that might be I plan on either the Poutine or the ATX smash burger. They both look fantastic.
For now, I think 4 stars best describes my grade for Pit and Tap. I liked it, but think theres a real chance that they could bring this rating to a 5 in the future with a strong showing my next time around

From the moment I walked in, they were friendly, what a great service and overall vibe
Super great people here.

Richard let me tell you talk about having not a great time but great company
He’s great !! Thank you for your humble and kind service!!
Will definitely come back only took this as my first time to experience a great experience with Pit crew .  The WINGGGGGSSS are a must have !!!  Also, heard there’s a karaoke night on Thursdays, so we’ll be coming back to experience that!! Follow up to come soon
Our go to place for bbq in downtown Wilmette. Great food, great service and really fun karaoke nights!

⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

Pierce at The Pit Tap is an absolute rockstar! From the moment we walked in, he made us feel welcome and taken care of. His attention to detail, friendly personality, and genuine passion for great service really stood out. He checked in just the right amount—never overbearing, but always there when we needed something. You can tell he truly cares about the customer experience and takes pride in what he does. Pierce made our visit memorable, and we’ll definitely be coming back because of him. If you’re lucky enough to get Pierce as your server, you’re in for a great time!

We came for a quick bite during happy hour and service was fast and friendly. All staff greeted us and served us. Our waitress Bianca was sweet and talked with us about the menu. Overall, great 10/10 experience and we’d come back.

First time for us, great draft beer selection and bartender was friendly and attentive. We started off with the pulled pork nachos. Believe they were made in-house chips and they would have been good but were so oily. Pork was ok, plenty of it but we wouldn't get it again. They have four sauces they put out for you to use with your meal, which is nice.  We got the pastrami and the brisket plates, (meat with a side of your choice, cornbread and pickles). Broccoli salad was good, like a Sunday church social flashback. We didn't like the beans and both meats were a bit tough and dry. There was a smoke ring on the brisket, which you want to see but maybe cooked too fast/too hot?
Pickles were good and the cornbread was ok. Nothing was bad, just not what we had hoped.

The Ribs and Mac & Cheese were delicious, although I would have preferred a spicier sauce. The slider also tasted great.  However, the cornbread was a bit dry for my liking.  The service was good, but I found everything to be a bit expensive.

Tapas Barcelona has a lively atmosphere and very friendly service. We tried some of the popular dishes including the highly recommended paella. While the food was good, it just wasn’t quite our personal favorite. Still, it’s a nice spot to try if you enjoy Spanish tapas.

I really liked the bacon wrapped dates.  They had a balanced blend of sweet and salty flavors.  I was a little disappointed in the paella.  It was good for Chicagoland but lacked some of the crispy goodness I’ve gotten from paella from elsewhere, 7 out of 10.  The empanada in the picture was very tasty, 9 out of 10.

Our favorite rsstaurant in Evanston. We love the food there. Pincho de solomillo is my favorite. The potato salad, berenjenas, salmon and jicama salad are our usuals. We really like the empanadas and their croquettes as well. Their desserts are also very good and the pear is a must (I might even say that one of my favorite restaurant dessert in the Chicago area). Considering that it is a tapas place portions are actually pretty good. Three tapas for two people is quite filling. Super nice and accomodating service.

Tapas Barcelona — the food is absolutely delicious with bold, vibrant flavors. I really loved the pasta sauce, and the ribeye was grilled to perfection. I paired it with Spanish beer, which made the whole meal feel super refreshing. The prices are reasonable, the food comes out quickly, and the service is great. I’ll definitely be going back!

Awesome tapas place! All the food was really good and fresh and the sauces on all the dishes are amazing for dipping bread (the bread is free!). A good number of vegetarian dishes as well! We also got a pitcher of sangria which was really good and    gave 3 of us 2 really full glasses.

I finished three tapas and a glass of sangria, and I have been recommending to everyone who might be going to Evanston. I’m definitely going again if I’m in the area. Grilled octopus and beef meatballs are must-haves.

2nd visit: As said before, I got the opportunity to come to the area again and I went to the restaurant for the second time. The grilled octopus hasn’t changed a tiny bit and I just LOVE it so much. Grilled baby lamb chops were cooked to the best texture. The dessert Bizcocho Borracho was amazing.

We came for a friend birthday dinner celebration, we enjoyed a lot!

The food were delicious!  I especially loved the seafood paella, steak and lamb

The sangria was incredible, i keep drinking and I didn’t taste any alcohol until too late lol

The waiters were nice

Depend on where your table, it can be a little tight or roomy lol

Parking is a hit or miss, no parking lot you will need to find street parking!

Would definitely recommend this Spanish restaurant!

ABSOLUTELY LOVE IT!!! This used to be my favorite restaurant when I was in college 14 years ago and I still remember it being such a treat to eat here on a Friday evening. After nearly 15 years my husband and I were finally able to come back to Evanston and the food here was just as delicious as I remember! The baked goat cheese is one of my favorite dishes of all time and the sangria is fantastic! I wish we lived closer because this would definitely be my “go to spot”.

Fish tacos great, margarita perfect. A date/3 girls could totally split this entree and feel full. Exactly what you would expect from a cozy local spot. Super clean, pretty outdoor seating with fireplaces. Pleased with my pick in checking it out!

This is a hidden gem of a brunch place. There are so many good options for food, including vegetarian dishes. The alcohol options are also great. This would be a great place to come with a group of friends to day drink and/or watch a game. The staff is also super friendly!

A festive restaurant with both outdoor and indoor tables. Menu offers salads, burgers, drinks app,..etc. We had the sliders, shrimp, ahi tuna and another other salads. All delicious with great flavors. Appropriate portions. The server we had was ok given not many customers. I would have given 5 stars if he was more attentive. Overall, we'll come back for the burgers.
Great location with cozy outdoor seating in Evanston!! I tried the Brussel Sprout Tacos and they were delicious and had a great portion size!

The food was pretty good. I ordered the stacked chicken sandwich along with a side of sweet fries. There was no sauce provided, I think they forgot. But the sandwich really filled me up, it's more than enough foenone person, not less than two servings.

Wow! 🤩 Head on over to this spot for some yummy grub! From the cheerful service to the flavorful food, yummy!!! Appreciated that the place itself has booths, free standing tables, and high tops. It’s quaint. The bathrooms are pristinely kept. The service was excellent & we were a bit needy-ish today. lol 😂 Great spot! We have enjoyed this two times now & had consistently excellent service & food! Plenty of free parking along side of the building, under the Metra tracks.

I have no complaints as I enjoyed my brief time at this establishment. I ordered the chicken quesadilla which was really tasty. It is close to Northwestern so I believe lot of students and staff frequent this place. The price was fair and customer service was good. They also have a nice happy hour menu!

First time at Stacked & Folder, my wife and I sat at the small bar to have a drink and appetizer. We shared the guacamole and chips at $12.95. It was tasty, but the chips were greasy, like they had been deep fried twice. For a college town restaurant, I think it is a little pricey. If you order only two tacos with rice and beans it will run you from 12.00 most at $16.00 and one at $17.00. Our guacamole and chips were $12.95 and not a huge order. If you want a Kobe Beef burger with one side will run you $17.95 or $18.95. If you don’t mind a regular quarter pound burger $11.95 or $15.95 for two Pattie’s.
For a cheap date night dinner with only two drinks we’re talking probably tax, tip, total over $60.00.
Yes, I’ll return to try more on their menu especially those Kobe Beef burgers. Reading several other reviews, there was a consistent complaint of dried out bread and buns. If it was me, I’d ask the manager to give me fresher bread 🥯
Before you go, look 👀 below 👇 and give this a thumbs up 👍. You can follow me to see many more reviews. I have over 4 million views.

We were driving around and found this place and it was open late kitchen. Quartet jazz playing while we ate. The food was very well seasoned. The service was very fast fast. Everything was tasty. The staff was very accom. A dating I'm most definitely will be back to try more food on the menu and listen to the entertainment Monday night Thursday night Friday night Wednesday night.

Food was okay here but this establishment charged my credit card $104 for a $45 meal. I don't appreciate having to take time to file a dispute to have that money refunded. Service was lacking here... I usually am willing to be understanding about that, but not if there are major errors in overcharging.

Came here after work to unwind and it hit the spot. The vibe is relaxed with a nice bar setting—perfect for decompressing after a long shift. On my first visit, I tried the steak frites for the first time and paired it with their Pineapple Margarita Jar—both were on point. The steak was tender, the fries were crispy, and that marg was the perfect mix of sweet and strong.

Came back a second time and grabbed the calamari, a $7 slider, and fries. Everything was fresh and flavorful. This time I went with the Strawberry Margarita Jar and it did not disappoint. Fast service both times, friendly staff, and you really can’t beat happy hour every day. Definitely adding this to my after-work rotation!
If you’re hungry, order here I guess. Service was uninterested and the food was really subpar. My burger didn’t have any onions like it was supposed to. Just find a different tavern imo
The “slider” burger is only $7 during happy hour but is really a full size burger with fries. The salmon chowder is amazing and unlike anything I had ever tasted. Go here please!!

I picked this place kinda randomly before seeing a musical act.

I made the reservation with gMaps for dinner on a Saturday, but ended up not needing it. It did get much busier.

There were so many upscale-lite dishes. They all sounded so good. So I freaked out, went basic, and got the steak frites. 🤣

Food was good, music was good, draft beers were good. Staff was great.

It got very busy, but never noisy. They have sound panels tactfully placed around the place and ceilings.

This place will get my return visit.

Stopped for an early dinner after a rainy tour of NW.  Excellent attentive service. Had the very flavorful trout and veggies, family ordered asparagus soup, mini crab cakes and tacos, Key Lime pie was also tangy and good. Good craft beer tap and bottle/can selection. Multiple seating areas, dining areas are downstairs, sidewalk seating per weather. I assume there is an elevator for accessibility.

Wish I could give 4.5 stars. The food was fabulous with generous portions. Wonderful setting but it's not easily accessible for aging parents down dark steps. The service missed a beat or two but otherwise a great meal with a menu that requires multiple visits. Also appreciate the obvious community engagement.

I’m surprised there’s a decent ramen place in downtown Wilmette, the quality isn’t bad. The soup stock is a little salty compared to the ones we liked in Japan, after all this restaurant is catered to Americans with much salty taste and not a fan of subtle taste like Asians. The prices are reasonable but wish they charge extra $2 dollars and give us little more noodles. Will return again.

On a Friday lunch the place has plenty of seats, don’t need a reservation.

We had a 5:30 reservation and arrived and were seated outside as requested at 5:25. Server immediately came and we ordered a couple drinks and an appitizer.  They were served within 3 minutes! Clearly the app had been sitting around. We said we were not in a rush but placed our dinner order. It was delivered to our table within 5-6 minutes and before we'd finished 1/2 our appitizer.  We actually laughed at how absurd this was. It should be noted that of the 5-6 tables outside only ours and one other were occupied.  By 5:45 the server gave us our bill and said "no rush," which was hysterical.  We took our time eating our dinner and left at 5:55.  This was the 8th or 9th time we've been to Torino but will never, ever go back.  Mistakes can be made but this was the rudest, most unprofessional service I've ever experienced.  Plenty of other options.

Honestly so amazing! First time ordering and we got two small sushi trays and mango tango veggie roll. We ordered off their site for a scheduled delivery and it came right on time and very much fresh! Everyone loved it and we will definitely order from here again!

There has been a huge drop in the quality of the food. Both portion sizes and food quality have gone down drastically in the past year. For ~$40 per person with appetizers and drinks it’s absolutely not worth the price. A shame since this used to be one of my favorite places in Wilmette.

This was my first time at Torino but it didn’t disappoint .
We were able to enjoy a gorgeous warm Friday night sitting outside, started with few starters : takoyaki, pork & shrimp bao, and curry ramen. Topped off with the best Japanese whiskey flight (my fav part), & separate bottle of clean sake.

Our server, Kyle, was attentive, friendly and great throughout our meal.

Everything was delicious and really hit the spot. I can’t wait to go back and try out some of other sushi rolls and ramen.
Also, big shout out for putting Japanese whiskey flight! That was absolute heaven tasting out some of my fav Yamazaki, Hibiki for decent price.
The food is amazing! My husband and I ordered the pork bao, two different kinds of ramen, and the octopus little appetizer. Everything was delicious. 100% recommended.

I had a pork bao bun and the Sammy ramen with sweet corn. I do think that the bao bun was missing something like shredded carrots. It needed something more. The ramen was absolutely delicious. I ate my entire bowl. It was that good. Our waiter was super friendly and attentive. Our food came out in a timely manner. I will say that inside, there were a lot of flies. Having worked in the industry, it's really important to have that under control especially if there is raw fish around. I also don't think that management was present in the front of the house. There were employees on their phones and eating in front of customers. I do think that was also distracting. That's why I gave a 4 instead of a 5. But I will definitely be coming back for more ramen.

Had a wonderful dinner, everything we ordered was fresh and delicious. Tried the bow buns, sushi, and ramen. The ramen was my favorite. Curry ramen was very flavorful, had  a few options to choose from.... Definitely coming back to try the rest of them. Gets busy on weekends. Recommend to make reservations
I ordered thai crunch and elewrap. Elewrap was good but thai crunch was a small box of dry veggies just veggies, no tofu and other stuff described in the menu.

I am not a vegetarian but I ordered here everyday during my trip to Evanston. The food is absolutely delicious. The salads are so rich with different ingredients of different textures and flavor. My favorites are the fried cauliflower, the fried tofu and the sweet potato fries. The smoothie is also very fresh.

As soon as I walked in I was greeted with great customer service! I ordered the buffalo chicken sandwich and was it delicious!!! I also was able to get a plant based cookie. Very moist and taste like the real thing. Will return! ☺️

Impressive place with amazing flavors! Didn’t miss the meat 🥩

Black bean burger was filling and well balanced. Love the red onion that brings the burger taste to the max.

Buffalo cauliflowers were slightly breaded and fried accompanied by carrots and a light ranch sauce.

Thai salad 🥗 yum 😋 the tofu was perfectly crisp topped with very fresh ingredients pulled together by the Asian vinaigrette.

How cute is the little note. 🦋💗🥰

Stopped in for a quick bite with my sister and tried the salad and cauliflower wings. The salad was fine—fresh but nothing memorable—but the wings were genuinely delicious: crispy, flavorful, and well-seasoned. The space has a cute industrial chic vibe, which adds to the casual charm. Service was slower than expected, especially given how empty it was, but not a dealbreaker. Overall, a solid option if you’re looking for a vegan-friendly spot with tasty plates and laid-back decor.

Our food was soooo delicious and Eric is incredible! Excellent customer service,  very kind,  appreciate that especially when spending my money. Nice chill environment and the bath room was clean. Makes me want to frequent often. Thank you so much!

This is our favorite restaurant for a quick and fun family meal. Our kid loves the Ele Burger kids meal with the impossible burger. Their burger and french fries rival McDonald's non-vegan counterparts. We also always order the BBQ Cauliflower wings and the yummy fountain drinks (orange cardamom, strawberry dragon fruit, and lemonade!). The milk shakes are awesome too!

elephant + vine has some of the best plant based food i have ever tried. the texture and taste of their plant based meats feel incredibly similar to the real thing and i found myself coming back multiple times. the staff members are such delightful people (and i totally recommend leaving them a nice message in the “special requests” section if
you order via kiosk). the only somewhat negative thing i’d say is that the prices are in fact, very chicago (definitely more expensive than your average fast food place).
Soooo delicious and they’re rice and beans is a MUST TRY !!! 3rd time here and I keep coming back. Very affordable too ! Definitely recommend this place. Very nice owners as well.
Best jerk chicken, ox tail, and beef patty I ever ate! Overall best Jamaican food that I have tried. I’ll definitely be coming back. Jackie is so kind and sweet to everyone who walks in.

Oh my! This might be the best Jamaican restaurant in Chicago, and its located in Evanston. Ordered a bunch of stuff last week, came back this weekend for more, that's how good their food is. Had the curry goat and that was well seasoned, moist, and delicious. We also had the oxtail and those were tender, seasoned to perfection, and scrumptious. We had the jerk chicken as well and that was moist and seasoned well. We had the chicken foot soup and it was 'transport me back to Kingston' good. We had the red pea soup this time and that was beautiful! My goodness they know how to cook in this restaurant. Beautiful food and beautiful friendly family running it. We drove an hour and a half for this food and we would do it again and again.

I moved to the neighborhood this summer and I’m so happy Spice is so close to me. I love popping by for lunch. Everything is good. I love the curry goat, but I’ve had curry chicken, brown stew chicken, oxtail, no misses. Everyone who works there is lovely and warm. Definitely check it out!

The jerk chicken is exceptional! The chicken is very tender and she makes her own jerk sauce with tons of flavor and a little kick at the end. The plantains were sweet and had a rich flavor. She added a little oxtail broth to our rice and beans which took them over the top!

The owner is incredibly sweet and uses a mix of her mothers and her own recipes! It’s some of the best Jamaican food we’ve ever had!

FYI the shop is devoted to the kitchen and counter serve. There’s a single table outside or a nice park across the street!
If you like spicy Caribbean food. you came to the right place. the food was amazing and customer service was fantastic. 5/5 would recommend it to everybody.

I must say the food and the customer service was outstanding!! Jackie the owner was very friendly and welcoming the food she makes is so delicious you can tell she makes her food with lots of love. Every bite tastes better than the last one! The oxtail was so good and flavorful I highly recommend it! Definitely will be coming back for the oxtails and jerk chicken.

Absolutely delicious to say the least!! Tastes like a home cooked meal. You can literally taste the love the owner puts into her cooking and she is so sweet. So happy I came across this restaurant, food, and atmosphere.  My boyfriend and I will definitely be back. Worth every minute of our 40min drive.

This place is absolutely amazing. The space itself is impressively large, offering plenty of room with super comfortable seating that makes it easy to relax and enjoy your time. The atmosphere strikes the perfect balance of cozy and lively, with a cute and inviting design plus lots of lounge-style seating for groups or solo visits. Service is quick and friendly, making you feel welcomed right away. Once seated, the food arrived in no time, and it was nothing short of delicious. Every dish was flavorful, fresh, and well-prepared, adding to the overall great experience. A fantastic spot to hang out, enjoy a meal, and soak in a warm and welcoming vibe.

This is a really good spot for coffee and they also have an excellent selection of pastries and other treats. I got the cinnamon roll and it was very good. The sweetness of the cinnamon roll perfectly complimented my mocha coffee which was excellent as well. This can be quite a busy place, but it's only because the coffee and food are so darn good. The wait wasn't really bad at all, only 10 minutes, and it was well worth it. So if you're in Evanston you can't do much better than this place for your morning coffee. Highly recommended!

We came here after playing some pickleball, and everything was fine. The soup was serviceable and the salad was a salad. I do appreciate that there was ample seating when we came on a rainy day, but the food and drinks seemed middling. Not too expensive which was appreciated, but I do think there are some places that I prefer nearby.

Cupitol Coffee & Eatery is a modern and stylish café with a great selection of espresso drinks and café fare. The interior is sleek and comfortable, with sidewalk seating that’s perfect for people-watching on a nice day. The coffee is consistently good, and the food menu offers fresh and tasty options for breakfast or lunch. Service is friendly and efficient, and the takeout and curbside options are convenient. Prices are reasonable for the quality and atmosphere, making it a popular spot for locals and visitors alike.

Great atmosphere, but lacking vegan options. I felt misled by reviews here and the older menus. Only vegan breakfast item is the avocado wrap and only if you omit the egg/cheese (and you’ll still be charged the full price). Even the oatmeal isn’t safe—it’s made with milk.

Food and matcha were OK
We tried a few items here.  None of those taste that great.  Compared to the price quantity wasn't good either.

Great food and menu. Really high prices ($9 for a small smoothie) but everything tastes excellent. $70 for a breakfast sandwich and smoothie for my girlfriend, and Corned Beef Hash and Poached eggs, coffee & smoothie for me. I asked for almond milk for coffee and they wanted to charge me which I thought was hilarious. Ordering process is chaotic and seating is on top of each other/cramped. Somehow I still like coming here because the food is so good.

Cupitol has it All. This delightful, clean, friendly and inviting establishment has everything you need to relax, sip excellent coffee and enjoy top quality food. Our first visit was 2 days ago and we’re back again. Premises are spacious, airy, yet carefully arranged seating creates spaces for conversation and collaboration. Cappuccino and cortado (yep - my usuals) are carefully prepared with a nice balance of robust and medium sweet arabica notes and rich crema. Americano was superb. Food is top notch prepared with farm fresh and organic ingredients. Omelettes are crafted in French style with smoky ham off the bone on mine. Fresh squeezed orange juice is excellent. Granola fruit bowl is delicious. Baked goods are solid - arrive early before pistachio croissants run out. A weekly menu of home-made soups stands out as soup seems to be a lost art. Excellent bread and salads along with many vegetarian and vegan options. Chilled and sparkling water available on tap for convenient and clean self-service. Prices are reasonable. If I had to pick one place in Evanston for all my meals this is it. Cupitol truly has it all and you deserve it - right??

An incredible restaurant to have amazing Mediterranean cuisine! The interior is designed with care, and all the workers were happy to help with any questions. I had the gyro and chicken platter over rice, which came with a huge portion of meat and other ingredients. You can’t go wrong with any protein here, and I highly recommend the falafel and hummus as well. The food comes out very quick, and it is always cooked fresh. Make sure to try Habibi In if you’re in Evanston!

I’ve heard about this restaurant from my niece for quite some time—she’s been dining here for over a year and always spoke highly of it. I finally had the chance to experience it myself, and now I understand why she kept recommending it.

From the moment I walked in, the warm and welcoming atmosphere set the tone. The highlight of my visit was the chicken kefta dinner, which was nothing short of mouthwatering. The meat was perfectly seasoned, tender, and juicy, with flavors that blended beautifully with the sides. Every bite felt thoughtfully prepared and authentic.

Equally impressive was the service. Mohammed, our server, went above and beyond to make sure everything was perfect. His attentiveness, friendliness, and genuine care added so much to the overall dining experience. Honestly, the kind of service he provided is rare these days—he deserves five stars on his own.

Overall, this restaurant exceeded my expectations in both food and hospitality. It’s the kind of place that makes you want to come back, not just for the dishes but for the people who make the experience so enjoyable. If you haven’t been yet, do yourself a favor and give it a try—you’ll see why it has such loyal regulars.
Awesome food! We ordered Habibi plate and it was delicious and enough for two people! Servers are polite and they have good amount of seating. I will recommend this place!
Excellent counter service Mediterranean food. The food is very delicious and has very large portion sizes. Staff is exceptionally friendly. Highly recommended.

There are so many things calling themselves inflation fighters. But in my view, there is nothing more qualified than the lunch special in Habibi In. Been a loyal customer for past five years and I knew they have been very fair in pricing. But dude, the lunch special is at next level. I'm even concerned that they'd go bankrupt with this offer. Regarding the food, always amazing, if not more. I'd even go one step further and say, if you have to choose what to eat for workday lunch, it needs to be this lunch special.

Yeah, you can’t go wrong here, the food was plentiful and it wasn’t oily.
Fresh, the service was excellent.
Ask for the pita.
When we come back, this is a must have.
I got the Habibi love 🎶🎶🎼🎶

One of the best meals I have had in a long time, for more reasons than just the food. Everything was delicious, fresh, and extremely flavorful (with huge portions for a great price), and the presentation was just amazing. In addition, the guy at the counter was just one of those people who seems to serve everyone with joy and happiness. Even though the food we were served was hot and fresh, the wait was almost nothing, and they continued with their fast service even through a large dinner rush. Possibly the best Mediterranean food I have ever had. Do not miss a stop to Habibi In and make sure to get the Habibi plate to get a taste of multiple of their amazing meats and veggies. Definitely will be coming back!
The food was insanely good. The shawarma wasn’t as good as the mixed grilled chicken over rice. Highly recommended for people who miss Mediterranean food.

Rooftop, great ambience. Good quality of food. Around $50/person (no alcohol)...includes desert. Big BBQ ribs, nice salad and amazing butter cake. The ambience make it spectacular place to re visit. Thank you.

In town from Nashville. Great vibe on the rooftop with exceptional service. Highly recommend the nachos for the table, a warm butter cake to split with your neighbor, and any salad if you’re still hungry!
Also, the maple old fashioned is a recipe I hope to recreate back home!

They offer a decent food menu, a great drink menu and a fantastic location/view. The prices are slightly high, but the portion sizes are big & plentiful.
We had the Lulu's Ginger Chicken Salad, BBQ ribs, Nachos and Double Cheeseburger.  The drink pictured is called "Yes, Please", and that's exactly what it makes you say after one sip!

Absolutely delicious food and good, strong drinks. Service was subpar, which was disappointing and unexpected! Our server checked in on us maybe *once* in our two hours there. I had wanted to order a second drink but never got the chance because they never returned to our table. I also went without water for most of my meal. We asked for a receipt, too, and never got it.

We came here for drinks for my bachelorette night-out, and it was wonderful! They quickly accommodated our group of 8 with a table on the roof top, and our server Grace was spectacular. Grace gave great recommendations and matched our energy perfectly! The decor, lighting, and ambiance on the rooftop for a girls’ night out for drinks was perfect. The drinks were also delicious - I got the “Yes Please” and “Yuzu Spritz” which were both amazing. I highly recommend this spot!

So cute and a great little rooftop. Restaurant was busy but the service was good. Zoie was our server, and she was great. Had the Beyond burger and the Lulu's salad, which is always a winner with that ginger dressing. The OG Margarita was excellent. I wish that you had a choice to get all the items listed when you go to the QR code to view menu. These are 3 restaurants that are all located together so when I'm at the Five and Dime, I also see the other two restaurants listed and food on menu for Taco Diablo and Lulus but those items are not available to order. Good marketing but slightly confusing. That being said, great rooftop, excellent atmosphere, and service. Would not hesitate to go again.
We hosted a meet and greet for our wedding guests at the five end dime. We worked with Carlos to arrange everything. He was fantastic and the staff, food, and atmosphere exceeded our expectations.

My parents were in from out of town and wanted to go somewhere that pleased all. This place was awesome. Started at the rooftop of five and dime for drinks and a view while we waited for our table downstairs. We were seated on the Blue Horse Tavern side and we loved the ambiance! The menu is the same through out all restaurants so it was nice to have variety. Our server Derrick was super nice and when I asked for recommendations was happy to let us know his favorites. Coming back for sure when the weather turns! 10 out of 10.

This is the spot to go to if you want healthy eats without having to interact with anyone, particularly good for those days you don’t feel so social.. :)

Order online or on the tablet inside the store, then wait for your order to be ready and pick-up your food at the counter. (I didn’t interact with anyone during this visit, but others have interacted with staff during their visits, according to their reviews).

Greek chicken was tasty- wish there was a bit of balsamic added, but was still pretty good. To me, it was a huge portion for the price- loved that. Food was ready earlier than scheduled time, which was great because I was in a rush.

Would eat again. Highly recommend.

As a young person, I ordered a salad that is very expensive for me to treat myself. However, I was charged full price while they didn’t give me 2 different items that I was supposed to get. One of them was an extra charge - marinated cannellini beans. Another was shallots, something vital to the flavor of the salad. I’m feeling very disappointed because there’s now no protein in this salad, only veggies. It isn’t really a complete meal without some sort of protein. Please do better next time.

I was a big fan of picnic for the last year or so, but they've frankly gotten quite a bit worse recently. Prices are higher now, portions are smaller, and they've changed what's in some of the bowls while forgetting to update on the menu (the avo & the egg doesn't have marinated beans anymore). To top it all off, I found a piece of plastic in one of my bowls. Hoping that they turn it around, so hopefully this is a wakeup call for management

I wish they have a loyalty program because I’ve become a loyal since the first time I visited.
This is the BEST salad restaurant I’ve had, especially I prefer warm and cooked ingredients and they’ve nailed that part. Their roasted vegetables are better than home made. Also loved the way they run the place—no dine in and no server so that they are focusing on the food quality.

Excellent place for salads/bowls takeout. Fresh ingredients always prepared to perfection. Looks good, tastes good, makes you feel good! No chain & locally owned always wins! No dine in at this location but you can go across the street and dine in at Pono Ono is what I was told! Pastries from Kiki Bakes Pie are likewise exceptional, no matter which one you pick!!
Tried Picnic for the first time today and it was amazing! I had the salmon with the miso dressing, and I think I found my new favorite spot. The food was so fresh and the flavors were 10/10.

I work in downtown Evanston, and I order from here most weeks (sometimes twice a week). The food is consistently delicious, and, as someone who cannot eat gluten, I really appreciate Picnic's diversity of menu options as well.

Picnic was my go to takeout place for years.  Then recently it was sold. And it has honestly gone downhill precipitously. The portions are significantly smaller.  The new food containers are not compostable or recyclable. They’re always out of bags and forks. It’s not what it was and the change is not good.

Carlos & Carlos in Wilmette was a good night out. We enjoyed the beef carpaccio, linguine with clams, and the meatballs—all well-prepared. Loved the sangria, and the service was excellent. We also tried the cannoli for dessert—beautifully presented, though probably not our favorite part of the meal. Overall, a good experience!

What a wonderful place for a night out. We went here for a nice Valentine’s Day dinner. The server was amazing and very knowledgeable, he helped me find the perfect wine. The bread was so crunchy on the outside but pillowy soft on the inside. I was so excited to try the scallops appetizer & they did not disappoint. I had the gnocchi for dinner and he had the shrimp pasta. Amazing & can’t wait to come back.
diversified italian dishes with a Latin fusion. great wine selection although they lacked a tad bit in wine knowledge but their intentions are good 😊 warm, affable and pleasant service.
Excellent food, delightful service, family environment. Highly recommend!!

Surprised how bad the food was this time
I had grilled calamari. It was the strangest looking  calamari I’ve ever seen, and it was rubbery and had no flavor. The texture was strange and the dish was doused in a tomato based sauce with hot diced pepper, red pepper and Greek olives, to cover the calamari’s strangeness.
Split a salad for $14 and it was really small.
Had egg washed veal and it had a peculiar flavor

Best Italian Restaurant in town.
Highly recommended.

I had the an exceptional experience here. A courteous gentleman, graciously recommended some dishes to us, which turned out to be delightful choices. He periodically checked in on us throughout the meal, ensuring our satisfaction. I highly recommend this restaurant.

So glad to have this family back in the area!  This is the second location for Carlos and Carlos and does not disappoint.  Customers in the area probably remember Capriccios and they bring the same great service and outstanding food. Mario and his staff do a great job and we will be back many times. Even during this tough time they managed to open and people will be happy with Carlos and Carlos highly recommend!

Omg I LOVE the Celtic Knot! Authentic Irish food and the nicest staff! Every time I go, and I’m there often, it’s the best day ever! My favorite is the corned beef, salad with pesto salmon and the huge and authentic Irish breakfast! Best pint of Guiness in Chicagoland. Two thumbs up for a wonderful establishment!

Right proper pub. Rich was our server and was an absolute delight. He recommended the curry fries to go with our drinks. The curry fries were delicious and I ended up wiping the little curry cup clean. Great atmosphere with good eats and great drinks selection (and pricing!). Ideal for a happy hour or a nice, cozy meal.

My baby and I went to The Celtic Knot and really enjoyed it! He had the chicken salad, and I went for the grilled cheese—both were tasty. The space was well-lit and cozy, and the service was friendly. For Evanston, it’s a really nice spot. We’ll be back!

Such a lovely experience. the waitstaff is fantastic, so attentive and personable. the food is consistent and absolutely delicious. the atmosphere is beautiful and so cozy, and the live music is always great.  this is truly my favorite spot in evanston, i leave with a smile on my face every time. you must go here, you won’t regret it!

Unique spot in Evanston! The hostess here is super nice and accomodating. Pretty busy but still a cozy and warm environment. We ordered burgers and had some good draft beers and stayed for a bit to listen to the live music.
So glad they are back and in a much better location! Best fish and chips in town! Fried pickles were great! Can’t wait to try the Irish Breakfast and corned beef!! Highly recommend!!
Corned beef and cabbage is excellent.  It is a warm and inviting pub and grill.  With great uris fare and drink.
Good Irish grub, very friendly staff, and kid friendly. Glad they stayed in Evanston. Patio is nice as well. The battered fried pickles were excellent

We had a wonderful experience here at TOMO! The ambience inside the restaurant is very casual, and the workers were super friendly. We had takoyaki to share, and I got the must-try karaage ramen. The food came out very quickly and was so delicious. The broth was rich and creamy, and the ramen was topped with a healthy portion of karaage. If you’re in the mood for a lowkey place to enjoy fresh Japanese cuisine, come here!

Lovely tiny gem. Ate by myself after work and enjoyed the lava takoyaki & tempura udon. The octopus was delicious but the shrimp from the tempura was tough. I originally ordered soft shell crab bao buns but was then told they were out of crab. Wish they led with that, my only real complaint because I was craving crab.

Wow! What an amazing experience at TOMO. Highly recommend this place for authentic Japanese street food, I ordered the lunch special  panko shrimp bento box that includes rice, goyza, salad, miso soup and shrimp and it was fantastic, delicious and worth the price. We also tried their karaage Ramen and was blown Way by the broth and the fresh Ramen and perfectly fried chicken! We also tried their friend chicken bun 10/10 delicious flavors! Will return to try even more items on the menu.

Picked up lunch looking for some comfort food, so ordered the Katsudon, and it was incredibly disappointing. The pork cutlet was over breaded, overcooked, and underseasoned, while the curry was also bland with vegetables cut far too big for a dish you’re supposed to be able to eat with a spoon. The flavor also left much to be desired, and the potatoes managed to be incredibly overcooked while the rest of the vegetables were nearly raw. I can only hope that dining in provides a better experience, but this put me off enough that I won’t be trying that.

We had a great lunch at Tomo. They were super accommodating when we needed to bring our huge baby stroller in.
The service was friendly and attentive, and the value in the lunch bento can’t be beat.
We will definitely be back!

5+5+5🌟

It really had the feel of a small eatery in one of the quieter regions of Japan. Chris the owner wanted to give a realistic experience. His wife who is of Asian descent, also a veteran of the food business, had a huge input on the menu. And, it is a wonderful menu.

I had the teriyaki steak bowl, also the cucumber salad, some hot sake to drink, and, the black bean paste dessert. Very sweet.

My wife, she had the octopus, the cucumber salad, green tea, and a very delicious Japanese guava juice. The facility is very clean, it is small, but they have a large room in the back for karaoke. By the way the bathrooms and the kitchen were extremely clean. That tells you all you need to know about the compassion of the owners. All in all, it was a wonderful experience. It really did remind us of Japan when we went to visit our daughter.

One thing I will mention, they do have a day, Tuesday, where there is an English conversation dinner for all non-native English speaking students going to northwestern. It's like everyone getting together and learning about everyone else. It's a very United Nations type of feel. What a wonderful idea! 🫶

Had a special dinner and splurged with 2 appetizers, 2 entrees, 2 desserts, and a hot sake and tipped generously bringing the total to about $50 a person and was very satisfied with everything. Could have easily spent less than $20 on getting just entrees and been just as happy.
The food was excellent and very hight quality for "street food".  I loved the atmosphere with it's perfect retro Japanese city pop music.  I can't wait to come back and get the full experience in their private karaoke room.

A cute Japanese restaurant located in downtown Evanston. We ordered ramens and octopus balls. Fairly tasties. The service was good. The server was attentive. The prices were average as expected for the type of dishes. The Japanese anime and music were not for me. Overall, I will be back.

Taverna Naxos is a charming Greek restaurant with a warm and inviting atmosphere. The menu features classic Greek dishes that are well-prepared and flavorful, from fresh seafood to hearty traditional entrees. The service is attentive and friendly, making diners feel welcome from the moment they arrive. The restaurant is a great choice for both dine-in and takeout, and the no-contact delivery adds convenience. Prices are on the higher side, but the quality of food and overall experience make it worth it. A solid option for anyone craving authentic Greek cuisine.
Pricey, but totally worth it. Food is amazing. Best octopus I've ever had. Added acoustic treatments make a huge difference to the atmosphere. Great that they added an outdoor area.

I rarely leave negative reviews, but this experience was disappointing. My group came in and ordered salads, which were listed at a certain price on the menu. When the check came, the prices had been changed without anyone informing us ahead of time. Transparency is a basic expectation at any restaurant, and adjusting menu prices after an order has been placed (and without notice) feels misleading.

The food itself was fine, but the lack of honesty really overshadowed the meal. Unfortunately, this experience makes it hard to recommend the restaurant.
Very cozy small kitchen with a gourmet flair on traditional Greek dishes everything was good totally recommend.

Nice atmosphere! Lovely staff, came to check on us a few times.
A little loud inside but very clean and cute.
Good spanikopita
Our stuffed peppers were a bit bland. Köfte meatballs were tasty but should be grilled longer. Many people ordered the fish which they debone tablesixe- we will try that next time.
Yummy baklava and Greek salad!
Will go back. Nice addition to the neighborhood.

The food here is absolutely fantastic! We just returned from Greece, and the food here is just as good. Highly recommend! The service is excellent as well. We look forward to returning.

We had the dips, spanakopita, beets salad, octopus, scallops, and grouper. All of them were amazing!

Down from the The Colorado Lamb, Greek Lamb, Salmon, My old fashion drink was original, I have not had an original drink in so long.  Our waitress was amazing & so was the service. My family and I will be definitely coming back for more. Just wonderful. Recommend this resturant to anyone who is in town or just wants Greek food around Willamette.

The food is outstanding. One of the best Greek restaurants I have ever been to. Some of the dishes that we all ordered-grouper, grilled octopus, saganaki, stuffed peppers, pork slouvaki.  The food was so pure and fresh.
The service was perfect.  Our waiter was so nice and helpful. The outdoor area was beautiful. We will definitely be returning.  Thank you.
